(588, 253, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:9:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:3:\"340\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:3:\"240\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"3\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"3\";s:11:\"tab_content\";a:1:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:704:\"&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Castle&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ajloun’s Castle (Qal’at Ar-Rabad) was built by one of Saladin’s generals in 1184 to control the iron mines of Ajloun, and to deter the Franks from invading Ajloun. Ajloun Castle dominated the three main routes leading to the Jordan valley and protected the trade and commercial routes between Jordan and Syria, it became an important link in the defensive chain against the Crusaders, who, unsuccessfully spend decades trying to capture the castle and the nearby village.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:1:{i:1;s:0:\"\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:1:{i:1;s:0:\"\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:1:{i:1;s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:36:\"Breakfast, Dinner and Transportation\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:4:\"200$\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:25:\"&lt;li&gt;200$&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:16:\"Breakfast, Lunch\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:2:\"20\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:23:\"&lt;li&gt;20&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"How To Pay ?\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:1:{i:1;s:12:\"How To Pay ?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:1:{i:1;s:13:\"PayPal . Cash\";}}}'),
