(114, 1, '2019-01-18 18:52:51', '2019-01-18 18:52:51', '<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Established in 1988, Ajloun Reserve is located in the Ajloun Highlands in northern Jordan, around the village of Umm al-Yanabi in the north of Ajloun.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is an area of rolling hills covered by dense woodlands of evergreen oak, interspersed with pistachio, carob, and wild strawberry trees. The trees have been important to local people for their wood, scenic beauty, and quite often for medicine and food. These woodlands are like the original forest animals, including herds of wild boar.</p>', 'Crazy Winter tour in Ajloun - 4 Days', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '112-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-01-18 18:52:51', '2019-01-18 18:52:51', '', 112, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2019/01/17/112-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
